[
    {
        "content": "<p>I seem to recall there is some way to view categories as monoid objects in a (bicategory?) of spans, could anyone enlighten me as to what I am half-remembering?</p>",
        "id": 201670317,
        "sender_full_name": "Callan McGill",
        "timestamp": 1592865996
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I learned this from <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"275899\">@Christian Williams</span> on Twitter, see <a href=\"https://twitter.com/c0b1w2/status/1201673784194822145\">this thread</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"inline-preview-twitter\"><div class=\"twitter-tweet\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/c0b1w2/status/1201673784194822145\"><img class=\"twitter-avatar\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1246894796796354560/SQX3u2hY_normal.jpg\"></a><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/ejpatters\">@ejpatters</a> my favorite monoid is a category\n - a monoid in Span(Set)(Ob,Ob)\n\nthis is using that not only in Cat, but in any 2-category K, the category of endomorphisms of an object is monoidal, with tensor given by composition.</p><span>- Christian Williams (@c0b1w2)</span></div></div>",
        "id": 201670465,
        "sender_full_name": "Evan Patterson",
        "timestamp": 1592866117
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See Section 4.2 of <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/math/0305049.pdf\">Higher categories, higher operads</a>, and especially Example 4.2.6 for a detailed look at this construction.</p>",
        "id": 201670630,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1592866281
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks both!</p>",
        "id": 201670727,
        "sender_full_name": "Callan McGill",
        "timestamp": 1592866354
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's fun to take the bicategory of spans of sets, look at a monoid object in it, and show it's just a category.</p>",
        "id": 201670747,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592866390
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For starters a span of sets is a pair of maps <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>O</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>O</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">s: M \\to O, t: M \\to O'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">s</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8777699999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">t</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 201670780,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592866436
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For the span to be a monoid object we need <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>O</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O = O'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.751892em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> so we get <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>O</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">s, t: M \\to O</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.80952em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">s</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">t</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span></span></span></span>.  (By the way, a monoid object in a bicategory is usually called a monad.)</p>",
        "id": 201670860,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592866471
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The multiplication of the monoid  object gives <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∘</mo><mo>:</mo><mi>M</mi><msub><mo>×</mo><mi>O</mi></msub><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ : M \\times_O M \\to M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.44445em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 201670879,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592866496
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>From then on it's a downhill slide: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span> is the set of morphisms of a category, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">O</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span></span></span></span> is the set of objects, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>O</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">s,t: M \\to O</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.80952em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">s</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">t</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span></span></span></span> are the source and target maps, and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∘</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.44445em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∘</span></span></span></span> is composition of morphisms.</p>",
        "id": 201670939,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592866539
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cool, thanks! Is there any particular reason you prefer to call that a monad? Is it just because that concept precisely describes the situation where you are dealing with the endomorphism monoidal category in a 2-category?</p>",
        "id": 201671670,
        "sender_full_name": "Callan McGill",
        "timestamp": 1592867049
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A monad in the 2-category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Cat}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68611em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">t</span></span></span></span></span> is precisely a monad on a small category in the traditional sense.</p>",
        "id": 201672421,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1592867740
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I said it's usually called a monad, not that I prefer anything.</p>\n<p>People usually talk about a \"monoid object\" in a monoidal category, and a \"monad\" in a bicategory (or 2-category).</p>",
        "id": 201672431,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592867750
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A monad in a bicategory is the same thing as a monoid object in the monoidal category of endomorphisms of some object in that bicategory.</p>",
        "id": 201672519,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592867804
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's called a monad \"on\" that object.</p>",
        "id": 201672740,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1592867995
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Makes sense, thanks!</p>",
        "id": 201674971,
        "sender_full_name": "Callan McGill",
        "timestamp": 1592869938
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You don't get functors as the morphisms between categories from the bicategory of spans though - for that you need to look at the <em>double</em> category of sets, functions, and spans. (Then you can get even more: the double category of (categories, functors, profunctors) arises as a double category of (monoids, monoid morphisms, bimodules) in (sets, functions, spans).)</p>",
        "id": 201699241,
        "sender_full_name": "Rune Haugseng",
        "timestamp": 1592900730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A different way to get functors and natural transformations is as a <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1301.3191\">free cocompletion</a> under a suitable kind of Kleisli object.</p>",
        "id": 201812813,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1592976298
    }
]